div.div:
Structural Insight Paths
For a problem type (having metadata like change history & potential, complexity, definitions, certainties/assumptions, functions, intents/priorities, & structures), there is a set of adjacent structures that can abstract the problem metadata & therefore be used as a template to generate it.
For example, there is a set of definitions, constants, functions, priorities, & solution metric filters that will solve a particular problem type set.
This offers an alternative to learning, where new info is used to update a structure, because structural insight paths often produce correct structures to solve a problem. However the structural insight path can be updated with new/specific info once applied to the problem system, to be used like other learning methods - just like a neural network algorithm can be a general standard DNN, used to produce a structure of a 'correct weight set to predict a variable within an accuracy range', or the structure/algorithm can be updated to specialize for a particular problem type.
